  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Honduras Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The government of Honduras through its president, Mr. Juan Orlando Hern&#xE1;ndez, has declared a national emergency thru an executive decree celebrated in ministerial council on October 25, 2017. The departments under RED ALERT are: Bay Islands, Atl&#xE1;ntida, Colon, Cortes, Yoro and Gracias a Dios. This declaration of emergency was determined due to forecasts issued by the meteorological center that warn of the entry of cold front accompanied by large amounts of rain, thunderstorms and landslides in vulnerable areas on the north coast of the country. Soils are saturated with water as a result of the rains that have hit the Honduran territory in recent weeks, affecting water absorption capacity and causing flooding of houses, flooding of rivers, landslides, etc.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">distribution of hygiene kits (toilet paper, soap, bath soap, toothpaste, toothbrush, detergent, candles, matches, towel, hand towel, deodorant, hair brush, sandals, children sandals, menstrual pad package)</narrative>
  </description>
